symbols.meaning: Non-dualistic existence where beginnings and endings become indistinguishable; inside and outside exist simultaneously on the same continuous surface
Completion through incompletion; the perfect expression of the imperfect moment; both emptiness and fullness simultaneously
Existence as probability rather than fixed entity; simultaneously wave and particle depending on observation; entanglement across time-space
Beauty through brokenness; history incorporated into present form; transformation that honors rather than erases damage
Self-consumption that fails to complete; recursion that spirals rather than closes; the broken circle that creates unexpected openings
